      <h1 class='title'>Hate Crime</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='commons-written-statements-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HC Deb 16 September 2004 vol 424 cc1679-80WS</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_1679ws' title='Col. 1679WS &mdash; HC Deb 16 September 2004 vol 424 c1679WS' name='column_1679ws' href='#column_1679ws' rel='bookmark'>1679WS</a>
      <div class='hentry member_contribution'>
        <a name='S6CV0424P2_20040916_CWS2_158'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-shaun-woodward' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0424P2_20040916_CWS2_158' title='Link to this speech by Mr Shaun Woodward' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-shaun-woodward" title="Mr Shaun Woodward">Mr. Woodward</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para">To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department what plans the Government has to amend the law to protect<span class="italic">(a)</span> transsexuals,<span class="italic">(b)</span> people with learning difficulties and<span class="italic">(c)</span> people with disabilities from hate crime; and if he will make a statement. [186869]</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      
      <div class='hentry member_contribution'>
        <a name='S6CV0424P2_20040916_CWS2_159'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/ms-fiona-mactaggart' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0424P2_20040916_CWS2_159' title='Link to this speech by Ms Fiona Mactaggart' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/ms-fiona-mactaggart" title="Ms Fiona Mactaggart">Fiona Mactaggart</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para">All categories of people are already protected by the criminal law. In particular they are protected from violence and threats of violence by offences such as assault, actual bodily harm and grievous bodily harm. They are also protected from harassment by legislation, including the Protection from Harassment Act. In sentencing for these crimes, courts<a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_1680ws' title='Col. 1680WS &mdash; HC Deb 16 September 2004 vol 424 c1680WS' name='column_1680ws' href='#column_1680ws' rel='bookmark'>1680WS</a>
          take particular account of the vulnerability of the victim and the motivation for the crime. The Government has no plans to amend the law to apply differently or specifically to these groups of people.</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
